main event: Radar sighting of an unidentified object near Cannon AFB, New Mexico on November 6, 1957.
interesting points: The object was reportedly moving at a speed of 60-70 mph and faded out at 15-20 miles, The radar readings indicated that the object's size was similar to that of migratory ducks, An analysis suggested the radar return characteristics resembled those of birds, The sighting included a tracked object that moved southward up to 60 NM, Weather conditions were low overcast with good visibility.
witness description: military personnel including captains of various ranks
